uld be included, but I need to manage cleanup.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Optimizing file management in tests**\\n\\nI can utilize `Files.createTempDirectory` to create a temp directory and a file, then run `fileSystemView.getFiles(tempDir.toFile(), false)` to find the shell. After testing, I should delete the temp files. This setup ensures there’s always a file present, which is important since `FileSystemView.getFiles` wraps each entry in `ShellFolder` on Linux and Windows. I’m contemplating a try-with statement, but that might not work since `ShellFolder` isn’t `Closeable`. \\n\\nIn my code, I’ll include cleanup in the `finally` block. I’ll define the temp directory and file and check their existence carefully. Still, if I return a shell folder inside the try, it could lead to trying to access an icon after the file is deleted. I need to ensure that the icons and access work correctly, even with these deletions in play.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering temp file management**\\n\\nI’m thinking that the assertion for not null from the fallback is important. But, if I delete the file before calling `getIcon`, the method might still behave correctly. That gives me pause about when to handle the deletion. Maybe I should consider keeping the temporary file until after the `iconFor` call to avoid any issues. This way, I ensure that the icon retrieval process has access to the file if it’s needed. I'll have to weigh the implications of that decision carefully.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering file cleanup options**\\n\\nI’m thinking about using `deleteOnExit` to manage resources in the background registry, which could be fine. It seems like it might support native images, allowing us to avoid extra cleanup. The guidelines mention closing resources, so that’s something to keep in mind. If we can return the shell folder and delete the underlying file on exit, that could work. I’ll implement a fallback for this, but it adds `IOException` to the signature.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_x9UyxV3lojaP8ra0aWI1JhXt|fc_09d6c009467515a1016a00cec1c80c819d96f64f8e6940a0ff", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/com.formdev/flatlaf/3.7.1/src/test/java/com_formdev/flatlaf/FlatFileChooserUIInnerFlatShortcutsPanelTest.java", "edits": [{"oldText": "import java.lang.invoke.MethodHandles;\nimport java.lang.reflect.Field;\nimport java.util.function.Function;", "newText": "import java.lang.invoke.MethodHandles;\nimport java.lang.reflect.Field;\nimport java.nio.file.Files;\nimport java.nio.file.Path;\nimport java.util.function.Function;"}, {"oldText": "    private static File findShellFolder() {\n        FileSystemView fileSystemView = FileSystemView.getFileSystemView();\n        for (File file : fileSystemView.getChooserShortcutPanelFiles()) {\n            if (isShellFolder(file)) {\n                return file;\n            }\n        }\n\n        for (File file : fileSystemView.getFiles(fileSystemView.getHomeDirectory(), false)) {\n            if (isShellFolder(file)) {\n                return file;\n            }\n        }\n\n        throw new IllegalStateException(\"Unable to find a ShellFolder test fixture\");\n    }\n", "newText": "    private static File findShellFolder() throws IOException {\n        FileSystemView fileSystemView = FileSystemView.getFileSystemView();\n        for (File file : fileSystemView.getChooserShortcutPanelFiles()) {\n            if (isShellFolder(file)) {\n                return file;\n            }\n        }\n\n        for (File file : fileSystemView.getFiles(fileSystemView.getHomeDirectory(), false)) {\n            if (isShellFolder(file)) {\n                return file;\n            }\n        }\n\n        Path tempDirectory = Files.createTempDirectory(\"flatlaf-shortcuts\");\n        Path tempFile = Files.createFile(tempDirectory.resolve(\"shortcut.txt\"));\n        tempFile.toFile().deleteOnExit();\n        tempDirectory.toFile().deleteOnExit();\n        for (File file : fileSystemView.getFiles(tempDirectory.toFile(), false)) {\n            if (isShellFolder(file)) {\n                return file;\n            }\n        }\n\n        throw new IllegalStateException(\"Unable to find a ShellFolder test fixture\");\n    }\n"}]}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 891, "output": 1323, "cacheRead": 41472, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 43686, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1778437810154, "responseId": "resp_09d6c009467515a1016a00ceb2e244819da746bfe72232a67d"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_x9UyxV3lojaP8ra0aWI1JhXt|fc_09d6c009467515a1016a00cec1c80c819d96f64f8e6940a0ff", "toolName": "edit", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Successfully replaced 2 block(s) in tests/src/com.formdev/flatlaf/3.7.1/src/test/java/com_formdev/flatlaf/FlatFileChooserUIInnerFlatShortcutsPanelTest.java."}], "details": {"diff": "     ...\n  14 import java.io.File;\n  15 import java.io.IOException;\n  16 import java.lang.invoke.MethodHandles;\n  17 import java.lang.reflect.Field;\n+ 18 import java.nio.file.Files;\n+ 19 import java.nio.file.Path;\n  18 import java.util.function.Function;\n  19 import javax.swing.Icon;\n  20 import javax.swing.JFileChooser;\n  21 import javax.swing.UIManager;\n     ...\n  69             restoreUiDefault(\"FileChooser.shortcuts.filesFunction\", oldFilesFunction);\n  70         }\n  71     }\n  72 \n- 73     private static File findShellFolder() {\n+ 75     private static File findShellFolder() throws IOException {\n  74         FileSystemView fileSystemView = FileSystemView.getFileSystemView();\n  75         for (File file : fileSystemView.getChooserShortcutPanelFiles()) {\n  76             if (isShellFolder(file)) {\n  77                 return file;\n     ...\n  83                 return file;\n  84             }\n  85        